  "prompt": "What is it like in Congo?",
  "response": "The Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) is a large country in Central Africa with complex challenges:\n\n1. Political situation:\n- Ongoing political instability\n- Frequent conflicts, especially in eastern regions\n- Weak government infrastructure\n\n2. Economic conditions:\n- High poverty rates\n- Limited economic opportunities\n- Rich in natural resources but poorly developed infrastructure\n\n3. Social challenges:\n- Low life expectancy\n- Limited access to healthcare\n- High child mortality rates\n- Low literacy rates\n\n4. Security issues:\n- Ongoing armed conflicts\n- Presence of multiple militia groups\n- Frequent violence in eastern provinces\n\n5. Environmental conditions:\n- Vast tropical rainforests\n- Diverse wildlife\n- Challenging terrain with limited transportation infrastructure\n\n6. Living conditions:\n- Many people live in rural areas\n- Basic living standards for most of the population\n- Limited access to electricity and clean water\n- Informal economic activities are common\n\n7. Cultural diversity:\n- Over 200 ethnic groups\n- Multiple languages spoken\n- Rich cultural traditions\n\nThe situation varies significantly between urban and rural areas, with major cities like Kinshasa having different characteristics compared to remote regions.",
